description:
The ISummaryCalculator interface defines the interface implemented by custom summary calculator classes. An instance of a class that implements this interface can be passed to the summaryOperation property of the SummaryField2 Class.

Implement the methods of this interface in two groups. The first group consists of the summaryCalculationBegin(), calculateSummary(), and returnSummary() methods. Use these methods to compute summary of the values.

The second group consists of the summaryOfSummaryCalculationBegin(), calculateSummaryOfSummary(), and returnSummaryOfSummary() methods. Use these methods to compute summary of summary values.

members.description: Flex calls this method to start the computation of a summary value. Use this Object to hold any information necessary to perform the calculation. You pass this Object to subsequent calls to the calculateSummary() and returnSummary() methods.

values: field The SummaryField2 for which the summary needs to calculated.
An Object initialized for the summary calculation.
